-- Sri Lanka's Hemas Holdings Rises to Record After First-Quarter Net Climbs
-- Anusha Ondaatjie
-- 2010-07-29T04:21:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-29/sri-lanka-s-hemas-holdings-rises-to-record-after-first-quarter-net-climbs.html

          
          
             Hemas Holdings Plc., a Colombo-based
diversified company, climbed to a record in Colombo trading
after first-quarter profit rose 61 percent.  
 Hemas Holdings rose as much as 5.6 percent to 42.25 rupees,
and traded at 41.75 rupees as of 09:45 a.m. local time on the
Colombo Stock Exchange.  
 Net income rose to 291 million rupees ($2.6 million) in the
three months ended June 30, compared with 181 million rupees a
year earlier, the company said after the market closed yesterday.  
